Nancy Kate Gutman and Steven Jason Matz were married March 10 at the Liberty Warehouse, an events space in Brooklyn. Rabbi Scott Shpeen officiated.
The bride, 32, works in Manhattan as the senior director of brand partnerships of the Los Angeles-based lifestyle brand Goop. She graduated from Union College in Schenectady, N.Y.
She is a daughter of Amy K. Gutman and Jonathan F. Gutman of Manhattan. The bride’s father, who is retired, was the founder and president of the Nandra Group, a brokerage firm on the floor of the New York Stock Exchange.
The groom, also 32, works in Manhattan as a manager for Amazon Web Services, the cloud computing division of Amazon. He graduated from the University of Florida in Gainesville.
He is a son of Mara D. Matz and Barry J. Matz of Miami. The groom’s mother retired as a middle school math teacher from Arvida Middle School in Miami. His father, who is also retired, was the president and a founder of Forms Processing, a company that provided data processing and document imaging in Miami.
The couple were introduced through mutual friends in June 2015 in Manhattan.
